quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  3,113,"Yet they are not all alike; some of the People of the Book are a nation upstanding, that recite God's signs in the watches of the night, bowing themselves"
  3,114,"believing in God and in the Last Day, bidding to honour and forbidding dishonour, vying one with the other in good works; those are of the righteous"
  3,115,"And whatsoever good you do, you shall not be denied the just reward of it; and God knows the godfearing"
  3,116,"As for the unbelievers, their riches shall not avail them, neither their children, against God; those are the inhabitants of the Fire, therein dwelling forever"
  3,117,"The likeness of that they expend in this present life is as the likeness of a freezing blast that smites the tillage of a people who wronged themselves, and it destroyed that; God wronged them not, but themselves they wronged"
  3,118,"O believers, take not for your intimates outside yourselves such men spare nothing to ruin you; they yearn for you to suffer Hatred has already shown itself of their mouths, and what their breasts conceal is yet greater. Now We have made clear to you the signs, if you understand"
  3,119,"Ha, there you are; you love them, and they love you not; you believe in the Book, all of it, and when they meet you they say, 'We believe,' but when they go privily, they bite at you their fingers, enraged. Say: 'Die in your rage; God knows the thoughts in the breasts"
  3,120,"If you are visited by good fortune, it vexes them; but if you are smitten by evil, they rejoice at it. Yet if you are patient and godfearing, their guile will hurt you nothing; God encompasses the things they do"
  3,121,"When thou wentest forth at dawn from thy people to lodge the believers in their pitches for the battle -- God is All-hearing, All-knowing"
  3,122,"when two parties of you were about to lose heart, though God was their Protector -- and in God let the believers put all their trust"
  3,123,"and God most surely helped you at Badr, when you were utterly abject. So fear God, and haply you Will be thankful"
  3,124,"When thou saidst to the believers, 'Is it not enough for you that your Lord should reinforce you with three thousand angels sent down upon you"
  3,125,"Yea; if you are patient and godfearing, and the foe come against you instantly, your Lord will reinforce you with five thousand swooping angels"
  3,126,"God wrought this not, save as good tiding to you, and that your hearts might be at rest; help comes only from God the All-mighty, the All-wise"
  3,127,"and that He might cut off a part of the unbelievers or frustrate them, so that they turned in their tracks, disappointed"
  3,128,"No part of the matter is thine, whether He turns towards them again, or chastises them; for they are evildoers"
  3,129,"To God belongs all that is in the heavens and earth; He forgives whom He will, and chastises whom He will; God is All-forgiving, All-compassionate"
  3,130,"O believers, devour not usury, doubled and redoubled, and fear you God; haply so you will prosper"
  3,131,And fear the Fire prepared for the unbelievers
  3,132,and obey God and the Messenger; haply so you will find mercy